I'm also a bit unsure why vim insists on the `new_buffer`; `free(buffer)`; `buffer = new_buffer` tango, like this:

``` c
size = 0x10000L;
for (; size >= 10: size /= 2) {
  new_buffer = verbose_try_malloc(size);
}
free(buffer);
buffer = new_buffer;
```

There must be a reason, but why not reuse `buffer`? (with `xrealloc` if necessary).
